##### MF33: COVARIANCES OF NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS                 6137 1451
                                                                  6137 1451
In MF33, we store the covariances of most, but not all, reaction  6137 1451
channels that are given in MF3. All covariances are generated     6137 1451
with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates TALYS runs using    6137 1451
a Monte Carlo parameter method.                                   6137 1451
For each MT-number, the information consists of:                  6137 1451
1. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Ea (variances)                6137 1451
2. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTa, Eb (correlations for the      6137 1451
   same reaction channel between different energies)              6137 1451
3. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Ea (correlations between      6137 1451
   different reaction channels for the same energy)               6137 1451
4. Covariances for MTa, Ea and MTb, Eb (correlations between      6137 1451
   different reaction channels for different energies)            6137 1451
Classes 1 and 2 are covered by NI-type subsubsections with        6137 1451
flag LB=5, followed by a LB=8 section which contains              6137 1451
the cross section variances multiplied by 1.e-3. Next, classes 3  6137 1451
and 4 are covered by flag LB=6 to account for the different       6137 1451
energy grids that two correlating MT-sections may have. Since     6137 1451
the total correlation matrix is fully symmetric, we only need to  6137 1451
include the correlation elements between different MT-numbers     6137 1451
once, and we do that in the subsection with the lowest of the     6137 1451
two MT-numbers. We include covariance information for all the     6137 1451
total cross sections, the lumped partial cross sections and the   6137 1451
individual inelastic cross sections per level (MT51,...). We do   6137 1451
not include covariances for MT600 and higher MT-numbers. For the  6137 1451
most important channels, we include cross-channel correlations.   6137 1451
                                                                  6137 1451
##### MF34: COVARIANCES OF ANGULAR DISTRIBUTIONS                  6137 1451
                                                                  6137 1451
In MF34, we store the covariances of the elastic scattering       6137 1451
angular distributions that are given in MF4/MT2. All covariances  6137 1451
are generated with the TASMAN code [kon12], which generates       6137 1451
TALYS runs using a Monte Carlo parameter method. The tables are   6137 1451
restricted to MT2 and contain covariances for the first 6         6137 1451
Legendre coefficients. Both intra- and inter-correlations of the  6137 1451
various Legendre coefficients are given. As in MF33, the LB5      6137 1451
representation is used.                                           6137 1451
                                                                  6137 1451
